comment: walkie talkies can be very effective for communication in situations where other methods such as cell phones or radios may not be practical or reliable walkie talkies are commonly used in outdoor activities such as camping hiking and hunting as well as in professional settings such as construction sites security operations and event management one of the main advantages of walkie talkies is that they do not require a cell phone network or other infrastructure to operate as long as the walkie talkies are within range of each other they can communicate effectively walkie talkies are also relatively simple to use and can be a cost effective option for short range communication needs however the effectiveness of walkie talkies can be impacted by several factors including the range of the devices the environment in which they are being used and the quality of the devices themselves the range of walkie talkies can vary depending on the specific model and frequency used with some models capable of transmitting up to several miles while others are limited to only a few hundred feet the environment in which the walkie talkies are being used can also impact their effectiveness as obstructions such as buildings or hills can limit the range of the devices additionally the quality of the devices themselves can impact their effectiveness with more expensive and higher quality walkie talkies typically offering better range and clearer communication
